a deal that was described as one of the largest deals ever for berkshire hathaway on march   berkshire hathaway made its first foray into the indian insurance sector with its nondirect subsidiary berkshireinsurancecom in the presence of warren buffett himself on february   berkshire hathaway inc and g capital announced plans to purchase hj heinz co for  per share or  billion including debt the company became a majority owner of heinz on june   after exercising a warrant to acquire  shares of common stock for a total price of  increasing its stake to  berkshire owns  million shares of gannett the company also holds part of newspaper publisher lee enterprises after buying some of lees debt after its bankruptcy filing on august   the boards of directors of berkshire hathaway inc and precision castparts corp unanimously approved a definitive agreement for berkshire hathaway to acquire for  per share in cash all outstanding pcc shares investment in apple incedit in may  it was revealed in a regulatory filing that berkshire had acquired a stake in apple inc the initial position was for  million shares  of apple worth  billion by the end of june  this stake had increased to  million shares  of apple berkshire then restarted buying apple stock again between september to december by  december  berkshire had built up a stake of  million shares  of apple with an estimated blended acquisition price of  per share aggressive stock purchases continued and by  march  berkshire had amassed a stake of  million shares  of apple in media reports buffett says that apple has developed an ecosystem and level of brand loyalty that provides it with a competitive moat and that consumers appear to have a degree of price insensitivity when it comes to the iphone investments in us airlinesedit in  berkshire surprised investors by making large equity investments in the major us airlines buffett had previously described airlines as a deathtrap for investors buffett had made an investment in us airways in  which although he sold for a profit almost lost berkshire a substantial sum of money as of  berkshire is currently the largest shareholder in united airlines and delta air lines and a top  shareholder in southwest airlines and american airlines buffett himself has described this as a call on the industry rather than a choice in an individual company american airlines ceo doug parker is said to have won over ted weschler in arguing that the airline industry had consolidated sufficiently and rationalised supply such that longer term profitability could be achieved in an industry that has historically been loss making in aggregate prior investmentsedit berkshire previously held a considerable stake in tesco plc the uk grocery retailer berkshire made its first investment in tesco in  and in  raised this stake to over  of the company with a cost for the investment of  billion buffett sold around  of this stake in  when he “soured somewhat on the company’s thenmanagement” realising a profit of  million as tescos problems mounted through  berkshire sold all the remaining shares with buffett saying to shareholders that the delay in selling shares was costly berkshire made an aftertax loss of  million on the tesco investment subsidiaries and equity holdingsedit main article list of assets owned by berkshire hathaway assetsedit main article list of assets owned by berkshire hathaway see alsoedit nebraska portal companies portal list of berkshire hathaway publications notesedit  a b c d e f berkshire hathaway inc  annual report form k xbrl united states securities and exchange commission february     berkshire hathaway portfolio tracker cnbc retrieved    warren buffett  annual report pdf p  retrieved  may    top  biggest conglomerates in the world based by revenue therichest  retrieved    the worlds biggest public companies forbescom retrieved may     berkshire hathaway forbes retrieved june     fuhrmann ryan  may  whats the most expensive stock of all time investope