 we invest in texas we invest big” said warren buffett chairman of berkshire hathaway “oncor is a great company with similar values and outstanding assets” berkshire hathaway inc already has a significant presence in texas with multiple headquarters in the state including bnsf railway company acme brick company justin brands inc mclane company inc berkshire hathaway automotive star furniture company tti inc charter brokerage liquidpower specialty products inc and allie beth allman  associates the allcash consideration for reorganized efh is  billion implying an equity value of approximately  billion for  of oncor and is subject to closing conditions including the receipt of required state federal and bankruptcy court approvals the transaction is currently expected to be completed in the fourth quarter of  greg abel berkshire hathaway energy chairman president and ceo said “this partnership combines the strengths of two companies that share a common goal of providing exceptional customer service and a commitment to invest in critical infrastructure that will make the texas energy grid even stronger and more reliable” effective upon closing of the transaction bob shapard ceo of oncor will assume the role of executive chairman of the oncor board and allen nye will assume the role of ceo of oncor “by joining forces with berkshire hathaway energy we will gain access to additional operational and financial resources as we continue to position oncor to support the evolving energy needs of our state” said shapard “being part of berkshire hathaway energy is a great outcome for oncor oncor will remain a locally managed texas company headquartered in dallas committed to the communities we serve and our customers will continue to receive the safe and reliable service they have come to expect from our dedicated team of employees” “we are excited to begin the regulatory approval process as this transaction has significant support across our key stakeholders” nye said “the stakeholders are eager to obtain a great outcome for texas” “we are pleased to be working with texas and stakeholders to ensure oncor continues to be a strong electric transmission and distribution company oncor is an exceptional company with great employees and an excellent management team” said abel you may also like researchers study links across us grids to move renewable energy… vestas receives mw us turbine order for midamerican energy’s wind… berkshire hathaway energy subsidiaries warren buffet’s fleet to deploy uptake… midamerican energy announces first two sites planned for wind xi… speak your mind cancel reply name  email  website enewsletter the wind team delivers up to the minute wind news wind resources wind product innovation and more upcoming events drone world expo  scheduled for october  to  in jan jose calif october   october  commerical uav expo oct  to   las vegas october    am  october    pm energytech  oct  to nov  october   november  view all events wind talk podcasts windpower editors paul dvorak nic sharpley and steven bushong interview the industrys biggest newsmakers and allow them to tell their stories click here to subscribe recent windpower articles new york governor plans transmission rebuild to enable more renewables alterra power completes financing  partnership for flat top wind project wind turbine common failures and solutions bachmann electronic shows solutions for smart turbines in husum sad news siemens gamesa to close blade manufacturing plant in tillsonburg ontario solar power world solar power world reaches executives managers engineers installers and technical professionals involved in the design manufacturing development and installation of solar power projects design world online design world online provides the latest design engineering news articles tutorials videos and products we help engineers and other industry professionals stay up to date print subscription stay informed stay smart stay aheadyoure invited to qualify for 